title: For Sale:  Remington 1903 Springfield
postcontent: There is no issue with high/low numbers and safe to fire as with Springfield Armory/Rock Island Armory. Overall this rifle features many correct Remington parts on an original barreled Remington 1903 with dark parkerization. The barrel gauges new with a ME of 1 and TE ~2 with CMP gauges. Rear Sight which smoothly adjusts with out sloppiness or play. I purchased these rifles for use in Springfield Matches and shooting and first and foremost wanted a good shooter with a new barrel and tight adjustable rear sights. Most CMP1903's I had inspected had been Greek refinished dark blue and featured well worn barrels with muzzle wear of 2-3+. The VFW returns I inspected were with a few exceptions more "correct" as issued with barrels fired with black powder blanks and pitted and dark bore barrels. Converted drill rifles came later and were considered unsuitable for reconversion to firing use. I have removed the grease preservative from the wood and metal, a many houred labor. Otherwise the rifle is how I purchased it from the CMP. I have found these 1903 rifles to be the most accurate of the US military issued rifles, including the M1 Garand, M14, and M16, only a 1917 with new bore will equal it in slow fire accuracy. With the barrel condition on this rifle it is unlikely to ever be worn out through shooting.

title: For Sale:  Bushmaster 450 New
postcontent:
New 450 Bushmaster Custom Build AR 15
This is a brand new custom built AR15 in the 450 Bushmaster caliber.  Total weight is a very light 6 lbs. 5 oz.    The upper is a Franklin Armory 7075-T6 aluminum forging made specifically for large caliber AR-15s like the Bushmaster 450 cartridge.  The upper features a factory oversized ejection port, factory installed dust cover, and forward assist.  The lower is a matching Franklin Armory 7075-T6 aluminum forging marked Multi Caliber.  The lower contains a tensioning screw that can be used to remove all clearance between the upper and lower creating a wobble free assembly.  The adjustable carbine stock, trigger guard, and grip are Magpul MOE in flat dark earth.  The Magpul stock can be adjusted to 6 different positions. The Magpul MOE grip has a storage compartment.  The lower parts kit is Milspec.  The aluminum free float hand guard is a 12” long key mod rail system in flat dark earth. The top of the rail is full length picatinny with 2 additional 3” long FDE key mod rails that can be attached anywhere along the sides or bottom of the hand guard.  The ported barrel is manufactured by custom barrel manufacturer Deadshot Barrels.  This 16” barrel is of the heavy contour style and is manufactured from 4140 Chrome Moly steel with a non-reflective armor black Cerakote coating.  The barrel is ported and therefore does not require a flash hider or muzzle brake.  The ports act as a muzzle brake which keeps the recoil down and since it is integrated into the barrel the overall length is kept to a minimum.  The barrel features a center feed ramp for proper feeding of the Bushmaster 450 cartridge.  The barrel is manufactured for a carbine length gas system with a .875” diameter gas block seat.  The underside of the barrel is dimpled for proper gas block alignment.  Rifle comes with one stainless steel 5 shot magazine.  Awesome looking and handling rifle.  Nothing to do but mount some optics and start shooting.  Rifle has been function fired to ensure proper function.
Payment: If local cash only.  Must have an active drivers license and sign a bill of sale.
If shipping is required I will ship to a licensed FFL holder of your choosing for $40 which includes insurance.  Payment can be in the form of USPS money order or cashier’s check.
